race.comment: TRAUMATISE (6) has an excellent record over this course and distance having never missed the placings in three starts, including two wins. Placed last time (30.42) at Angle Park in a Grade 5, finishing second and beaten 1.5 lengths. Looks a leading chance on best. TALCOTT BALE (2) has a strong record here with five wins and two placings from nine starts. Placed last time (24.75) at Sale in a Free For All, finishing second and beaten 1.1 lengths. Can feature in the finish. CANYA ULTIMATE (1) is worth forgiving for her last effort when eighth (24.29) at Bendigo over 425m. Got the money at her only try from this box. Can figure in the finish. WEBLEC JOEL (8) picked up a cheque last time and is in the mix again.
